##1.1 Objective
Cryptocurrency markets are highly volatile. 
This project builds a Machine Learning model 
to predict Bitcoin volatility using historical 
OHLC data, trading volume and market cap.

1.2 Goals
- Predict 7-day rolling volatility
- Help traders identify high risk periods
- Enable informed investment decisions

1.3 Dataset
- Total Records : 72,946
- Cryptocurrencies : 50+
- Focus : Bitcoin (3012 records)
- Features : Date, Open, High, Low, 
             Close, Volume, Market Cap


## System Architecture
Insert → SmartArt → Process → 

[Raw Data] → [Preprocessing] → [Feature Engineering]
     → [Model Training] → [Evaluation] → [Deployment]

## Technology Stack
| Category      | Technology          |
|---------------|---------------------|
| Language      | Python 3.10         |
| Data Library  | Pandas, NumPy       |
| ML Model      | XGBoost Regressor   |
| Scaling       | StandardScaler      |
| Visualization | Matplotlib, Seaborn |
| Deployment    | Streamlit           |
| IDE           | VS Code             |
| Environment   | Virtual Env (venv)  |

## Data Flow
Raw Dataset (dataset.csv)
         ↓
   Data Cleaning
   - Remove duplicates
   - Fix date format
   - Filter Bitcoin data
         ↓
   Feature Engineering
   - Moving Averages
   - Bollinger Bands
   - RSI, ATR
   - Lag Features
         ↓
   Train/Test Split
   - Train : 80%
   - Test  : 20%
         ↓
   XGBoost Model
         ↓
   Prediction Output

## Model Overview
Model     : XGBoost Regressor
Target    : 7-Day Rolling Volatility

Results:
┌─────────┬──────────┐
│ Metric  │  Score   │
├─────────┼──────────┤
│ RMSE    │ 0.007201 │
│ MAE     │ 0.004658 │
│ R²      │ 0.8183   │
└─────────┴──────────┘

Total Features : 23
Key Features   : volatility_lag1, 
                 price_range_pct,
                 BB_width, ATR_14,
                 RSI_14

## Deployment
Tool    : Streamlit
URL     : localhost:8501

Input   : Open, High, Low, Close,
          Volume, Market Cap

Output  :
🔴 High Volatility   → Value > 0.05
🟡 Medium Volatility → 0.02 to 0.05  
🟢 Low Volatility    → Value < 0.02

